  "time_ut": 1657935959,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dab\u0dba \u0db6\u0dbb \u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0dc3\u0db3\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ready to support Sri Lanka for debt relief",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "China declares that it is ready to work with relevant countries and international financial institutions to play an active role in alleviating Sri Lanka's current difficulties and debt burden and for Sri Lanka's efforts to achieve sustainable development.",
        "Mr. Wang Wenbin, spokesperson of the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs, said this while attending the daily press conference held by China.",
        "Further commenting on China-Sri Lanka financial cooperation, he said that shortly after Sri Lanka announced that it would suspend loan payments, Chinese financial institutions are ready to contact the Sri Lankan side to find a proper way to manage the matured loans received from China."
      ],
